    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The CFD model predicted the relative hemolysis index at the nominal operating point with a relative error of 2.3%, demonstrating excellent agreement with the single validation experiment. On the basis of this result, the model is validated for the full operating range of the COU, covering all five flow-speed combinations specified in the intended use. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 scoping guidance. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
